{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880577842,"sessionID":"ses_285489331ffe7fl4FcwAl9BTUV","part":{"id":"prt_d7abb1ea6001etuv5E5c2OUSZ3","messageID":"msg_d7abb1009001LAkbwu8Acyb1Qo","sessionID":"ses_285489331ffe7fl4FcwAl9BTUV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2e9724468a7346b6b8883836","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-035/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-035/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成\n2: \n3: **Module:** client-go\n4: **Language:** Go\n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: 为 AgentCube 项目生成标准的 Kubernetes 风格 Go 客户端库（`client-go`），提供对自定义资源 `AgentRuntime` 和 `CodeInterpreter`（API Group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`）的类型安全 CRUD 操作、事件监听（Informer）和缓存索引（Lister）能力。\n10: \n11: 该客户端库遵循 `k8s.io/code-generator` 的约定，使 AgentCube 的 Go 用户能够以与原生 Kubernetes 客户端一致的方式操作自定义资源，同时为 AgentCube 内部控制器和 Operator 提供基础的客户端基础设施。\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: ### In Scope\n16: \n17: 1. **Clientset 顶层入口**\n18:    - `Interface` / `Clientset` 结构体及构造函数（`NewForConfig`, `NewForConfigAndClient`, `NewForConfigOrDie`, `New`）\n19:    - `Discovery()` 和 `RuntimeV1alpha1()` 分组访问器\n20: \n21: 2. **Typed Client — `runtime/v1alpha1`**\n22:    - `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` / `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`（REST 客户端，`APIPath=/apis`）\n23:    - `AgentRuntimeInterface` — `AgentRuntime` 资源的完整 CRUD + Watch + Patch + DeleteCollection\n24:    - `CodeInterpreterInterface` — `CodeInterpreter` 资源的完整 CRUD + Watch + Patch + DeleteCollection\n25:    - `AgentRuntimeExpansion` / `CodeInterpreterExpansion` 空接口（预留自定义方法）\n26:    - Fake typed clients（`fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go`）\n27: \n28: 3. **Scheme 注册**\n29:    - `register.go` — 构建 `Scheme`, `Codecs`, `ParameterCodec`；`AddToScheme` 注册 `runtime/v1alpha1` 类型\n30: \n31: 4. **Informer Factory**\n32:    - `SharedInformerFactory` — `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync`/`ForResource`/`InformerFor`\n33:    - 构造函数：`NewSharedInformerFactory`, `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions`\n34:    - Options：`WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`\n35:    - Group/Version 访问器链：`Runtime()` → `V1alpha1()` → `AgentRuntimes()`/`CodeInterpreters()`\n36:    - Per-type Informer：`AgentRuntimeInformer`, `CodeInterpreterInformer`（含 `Informer()` + `Lister()`）\n37:    - Generic `ForResource` 路由（`agentruntimes` / `codeinterpreters`）\n38: \n39: 5. **Listers**\n40:    - `AgentRuntimeLister` / `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` — 基于本地缓存的只读索引\n41:    - `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister`\n42:    - Expansion 空接口（四个类型）\n43: \n44: 6. **Fake Clientset**\n45:    - `NewSimpleClientset` / `NewClientset` — 内存级 Fake Clientset\n46:    - Scheme 注册 wiring\n47: \n48: 7. **代码生成管线**\n49:    - `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n50:    - 使用 `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1，`--with-watch` 标志\n51:    - 输出包路径：`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n52: \n53: ### Out of Scope\n54: \n55: - 手写客户端逻辑（所有代码由 code-generator 自动生成）\n56: - API Server 端逻辑（CRD 定义、控制器、Webhook）\n57: - 认证/授权配置（由调用方通过 `rest.Config` 提供）\n58: - 自定义 Informer/Lister 扩展方法（Expansion 接口为空，由消费者自行实现）\n59: - 多 API Group 或未来版本的客户端生成（当前仅 `runtime/v1alpha1`）\n60: \n61: ## Architecture Summary\n62: \n63: ### Current State\n64: \n65: AgentCube 定义了 CRD 类型 `AgentRuntime` 和 `CodeInterpreter`（`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`），但尚未生成对应的 Kubernetes 风格客户端库。Go 消费者需要手动构造 REST 请求或使用通用 `dynamic.Client`，缺乏类型安全和 Informer/Lister 模式支持。\n66: \n67: ### Target State\n68: \n69: 生成完整的 `client-go` 模块，包含四层架构：\n70: \n71: ```\n72: Clientset (顶层入口)\n73:   └── RuntimeV1alpha1Client (分组 REST 客户端)\n74:         ├── AgentRuntimeInterface (typed REST)\n75:         └── CodeInterpreterInterface (typed REST)\n76: \n77: SharedInformerFactory (事件驱动)\n78:   └── Runtime().V1alpha1()\n79:         ├── AgentRuntimeInformer → AgentRuntimeLister\n80:         └── CodeInterpreterInformer → CodeInterpreterLister\n81: \n82: FakeClientset (测试替身)\n83:   └── 实现全部 Interface，内存存储\n84: ```\n85: \n86: 所有代码由 `k8s.io/code-generator` 从 `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` 的类型定义自动生成，通过 `// +genclient` 等 marker 控制生成行为。\n87: \n88: ## Impact Analysis\n89: \n90: ### 依赖影响\n91: \n92: | 影响项 | 说明 |\n93: |--------|------|\n94: | **新增模块** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` 作为独立 Go module 或子包 |\n95: | **传递依赖** | `k8s.io/client-go`, `k8s.io/apimachinery` (v0.34.1), `k8s.io/code-generator` (dev-only) |\n96: | **Go 版本** | 需与 code-generator v0.34.1 兼容（Go 1.22+） |\n97: | **构建系统** | `Makefile` 新增 `gen-client` target；`hack/update-codegen.sh` 脚本 |\n98: \n99: ### 消费者影响\n100: \n101: - **正向**：提供类型安全的客户端，消除手动构造 REST 请求的样板代码\n102: - **正向**：Informer + Lister 模式支持高效的本地缓存和事件驱动编程\n103: - **正向**：Fake clients 使单元测试无需真实集群\n104: - **风险**：API 类型定义变更后需重新生成客户端（通过 `make gen-client` 自动化缓解）\n105: - **向后兼容**：生成代码的接口签名由 CRD 类型决定；类型字段变更可能导致消费者编译失败\n106: \n107: ### 安全影响\n108: \n109: - 客户端本身不处理认证/授权，依赖调用方提供正确的 `rest.Config`（含 token/cert）\n110: - Fake clients 仅用于测试，不涉及生产数据\n111: \n112: ### 性能影响\n113: \n114: - Informer 全量 List 后 Watch 增量更新，初始同步时间与资源数量成正比\n115: - Lister 基于 `cache.Indexer`，读操作 O(1)（按 key）或 O(n)（按 selector 遍历）\n116: - 生成代码本身无性能开销，与手写等效\n117: \n118: ### 运维影响\n119: \n120: - 生成代码不应手动修改（`Expansion` 接口除外）\n121: - CRD 类型变更后需执行 `make gen-client` 重新生成并提交 diff\n122: - 生成的文件量较大（~20 个文件），但全部为确定性输出\n123: \n124: ## Alternatives Considered\n125: \n126: ### 1. 手写 REST 客户端（❌ 不采用）\n127: \n128: **做法**：手动实现 `AgentRuntimeClient` 和 `CodeInterpreterClient`，使用 `rest.RESTClient` 发送请求。\n129: \n130: **优点**：无外部生成工具依赖，可完全定制\n131: \n132: **缺点**：\n133: - 大量样板代码（CRUD + Watch + Patch + Options 构造）\n134: - 易出错，类型安全难以保证\n135: - 需自行实现 Informer/Lister 模式（复杂度高）\n136: - 与 Kubernetes 生态不一致，增加学习成本\n137: \n138: **决策**：不采用。维护成本过高，无法利用成熟的 code-generator 生态。\n139: \n140: ### 2. 使用 controller-runtime 的 `client.Client`（❌ 不采用）\n141: \n142: **做法**：依赖 `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client` 提供通用客户端。\n143: \n144: **优点**：更高层抽象，内置缓存和索引，与控制器框架集成紧密\n145: \n146: **缺点**：\n147: - 引入完整的 controller-runtime 依赖（较重，含 manager、reconcile 等）\n148: - 不适合仅需轻量客户端的场景（如独立 CLI 工具）\n149: - 动态类型（`client.Object`）不如生成代码的类型安全\n150: \n151: **决策**：不采用。AgentCube 的部分消费者可能只需要轻量客户端而非完整控制器框架。controller-runtime 可作为上层可选依赖。\n152: \n153: ### 3. 使用 dynamic.Client + unstructured（❌ 不采用）\n154: \n155: **做法**：使用 `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` 操作 `unstructured.Unstructured` 对象。\n156: \n157: **优点**：无需生成代码，支持任意 CRD\n158: \n159: **缺点**：\n160: - 无编译时类型检查，字段访问通过 map 操作\n161: - 代码冗长且易出错（`obj.Object[\"spec\"].(map[string]interface{})[\"replicas\"]`）\n162: - 无 Informer/Lister 的类型安全变体\n163: \n164: **决策**：不采用。类型安全性是核心需求。\n165: \n166: ### 4. k8s.io/code-generator 生成（✅ 选定方案）\n167: \n168: **做法**：使用 Kubernetes 官方 `code-generator` 工具从 `pkg/apis/` 类型定义生成客户端。\n169: \n170: **优点**：\n171: - Kubernetes 官方标准，与生态完全一致\n172: - 自动生成 Clientset、Informer、Lister、Fake 完整工具链\n173: - 编译时类型安全\n174: - 社区成熟，长期维护有保障\n175: - 与现有 `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` 类型定义无缝集成\n176: \n177: **缺点**：\n178: - 生成代码量大（~20 个文件）\n179: - 需维护 code-generator 版本和生成脚本\n180: - CRD 类型变更后需重新生成\n181: \n182: **决策**：采用。符合 Kubernetes 生态最佳实践，长期维护成本最低。\n183: \n184: ## Upstream Dependencies\n185: \n186: | 依赖 | 版本 | 用途 |\n187: |------|------|------|\n188: | `k8s.io/code-generator` | v0.34.1 | 代码生成工具（dev-only） |\n189: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | REST 客户端、Discovery、Fake 基础 |\n190: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | Scheme、Codec、meta 类型 |\n191: | AgentCube `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | 本地 | CRD 类型定义（生成输入） |\n192: \n193: ### 类型定义前置条件\n194: \n195: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` 需包含：\n196: - `AgentRuntime` / `AgentRuntimeList` 结构体及 `// +genclient` marker\n197: - `CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList` 结构体及 `// +genclient` marker\n198: - `SchemeBuilder` / `AddToScheme` 注册\n199: - DeepCopy 方法（由 `deepcopy-gen` 预先生成）\n200: \n201: ## Status\n202: \n203: - [ ] Proposal review\n204: - [ ] Implementation\n205: - [ ] Verification\n\n(End of file - total 205 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成\n\n**Module:** client-go\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** L\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 AgentCube 项目生成标准的 Kubernetes 风格 Go 客户端库（`client-go`），提供对自定义资源 `AgentRuntime` 和 `CodeInterpreter`（API Group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`）的类型安全 CRUD 操作、事件监听（Informer）和缓存索引（Lister）能力。\n\n该客户端库遵循 `k8s.io/code-generator` 的约定，使 AgentCube 的 Go 用户能够以与原生 Kubernetes 客户端一致的方式操作自定义资源，同时为 AgentCube 内部控制器和 Operator 提供基础的客户端基础设施。\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **Clientset 顶层入口**\n   - `Interface` / `Clientset` 结构体及构造函数（`NewForConfig`, `NewForConfigAndClient`, `NewForConfigOrDie`, `New`）\n   - `Discovery()` 和 `RuntimeV1alpha1()` 分组访问器\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-035/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775880577830,"end":1775880577839}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880579204,"sessionID":"ses_285489331ffe7fl4FcwAl9BTUV","part":{"id":"prt_d7abb23fc001NG2gZFmhkBV2Ep","messageID":"msg_d7abb1009001LAkbwu8Acyb1Qo","sessionID":"ses_285489331ffe7fl4FcwAl9BTUV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_c08070271d3c4e3dac291ae2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-035: client-go 类型客户端生成 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `client-go`\n6: - **Language:** Go\n7: - **Size:** L\n8: - **Base specs:** `deployment/client-go.md`\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers the generated Kubernetes client-go library for API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, module path `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`. It SHALL provide a typed Clientset, per-resource REST clients, SharedInformerFactory, Listers, and in-memory Fake clients for the `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources. All code SHALL be generated via `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` using `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Clientset\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: Interface contract\n19: \n20: The system SHALL provide a `Clientset` implementing `Interface` with discovery and group accessor methods.\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: Interface exposes Discovery and RuntimeV1alpha1\n23: - **GIVEN** the `Interface` type is defined in `clientset/versioned/clientset.go`\n24: - **WHEN** the interface is inspected\n25: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface` and `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Clientset struct embeds DiscoveryClient\n28: - **GIVEN** the `Clientset` struct is defined\n29: - **WHEN** the struct fields are inspected\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL embed `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and hold `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Clientset constructors\n33: \n34: The system SHALL provide four constructor functions for creating `Clientset` instances.\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: NewForConfig creates clientset from rest.Config\n37: - **GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config` pointing to a Kubernetes API server\n38: - **WHEN** `NewForConfig(c)` is called\n39: - **THEN** it SHALL return `(*Clientset, nil)` with all group clients initialized, or `(*Clientset, error)` on failure\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: NewForConfigAndClient uses custom http.Client\n42: - **GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config` and `*http.Client`\n43: - **WHEN** `NewForConfigAndClient(c, httpClient)` is called\n44: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `*Clientset` using the provided HTTP client for transport\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: NewForConfigOrDie panics on invalid config\n47: - **GIVEN** an invalid `*rest.Config` (e.g., malformed host)\n48: - **WHEN** `NewForConfigOrDie(c)` is called\n49: - **THEN** it SHALL panic\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: NewForConfigOrDie succeeds with valid config\n52: - **GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config`\n53: - **WHEN** `NewForConfigOrDie(c)` is called\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `*Clientset` without panicking\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: New creates clientset from rest.Interface\n57: - **GIVEN** a pre-configured `rest.Interface`\n58: - **WHEN** `New(restInterface)` is called\n59: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `*Clientset` with the typed client wired to the provided interface\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: RuntimeV1alpha1 group accessor\n62: \n63: The system SHALL provide access to the `runtime/v1alpha1` API group client.\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1 returns typed group client\n66: - **GIVEN** a `Clientset` instance\n67: - **WHEN** `cs.RuntimeV1alpha1()` is called\n68: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## Typed Client — runtime/v1alpha1\n73: \n74: ### Requirement: RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n75: \n76: The system SHALL provide a group-level interface exposing REST client and resource getters.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1Interface contract\n79: - **GIVEN** the `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` is defined in `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`\n80: - **WHEN** the interface is inspected\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `RESTClient() rest.Interface`, `AgentRuntimesGetter`, and `CodeInterpretersGetter`\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1Client implements the interface\n84: - **GIVEN** the `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` struct\n85: - **WHEN** its methods are inspected\n86: - **THEN** it SHALL implement all methods of `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: REST defaults are configured correctly\n89: - **GIVEN** a `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` instance\n90: - **WHEN** its REST client is inspected\n91: - **THEN** `GroupVersion` SHALL be `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion`, `APIPath` SHALL be `/apis`, and negotiated serializer SHALL come from `clientset/versioned/scheme`\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime typed client\n94: \n95: The system SHALL provide a typed REST client for the `agentruntimes` resource.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimesGetter interface\n98: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimesGetter` interface\n99: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface`\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Create\n103: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and a valid `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime`\n104: - **WHEN** `Create(ctx, agentRuntime, opts)` is called\n105: - **THEN** it SHALL POST to `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes` and return the created object\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Update\n108: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and an existing `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime`\n109: - **WHEN** `Update(ctx, agentRuntime, opts)` is called\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL PUT to the resource URL and return the updated object\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — UpdateStatus\n113: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and an `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime` with modified status\n114: - **WHEN** `UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, opts)` is called\n115: - **THEN** it SHALL PUT to the `/status` subresource endpoint\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Get\n118: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and a resource name\n119: - **WHEN** `Get(ctx, name, opts)` is called\n120: - **THEN** it SHALL GET the resource and return `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime`\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — List\n123: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n124: - **WHEN** `List(ctx, opts)` is called\n125: - **THEN** it SHALL GET the collection and return `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList`\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Delete\n128: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and a resource name\n129: - **WHEN** `Delete(ctx, name, opts)` is called\n130: - **THEN** it SHALL DELETE the resource and return `nil` on success or `error` on failure\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — DeleteCollection\n133: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n134: - **WHEN** `DeleteCollection(ctx, deleteOpts, listOpts)` is called\n135: - **THEN** it SHALL DELETE all resources matching `listOpts`\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Watch\n138: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n139: - **WHEN** `Watch(ctx, opts)` is called\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL establish a watch stream and return `watch.Interface`\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Patch\n143: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`, name, patch type, and patch data\n144: - **WHEN** `Patch(ctx, name, pt, data, opts, subresources...)` is called\n145: - **THEN** it SHALL PATCH the resource and return the patched `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime`\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime resource plural\n148: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime REST client\n149: - **WHEN** the resource path is constructed\n150: - **THEN** the plural form SHALL be `agentruntimes`\n151: \n152: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter typed client\n153: \n154: The system SHALL provide a typed REST client for the `codeinterpreters` resource with the same method shape as AgentRuntime.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: CodeInterpretersGetter interface\n157: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpretersGetter` interface\n158: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n159: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterInterface`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterInterface methods\n162: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterInterface`\n163: - **WHEN** its methods are inspected\n164: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `Create`, `Update`, `UpdateStatus`, `Delete`, `DeleteCollection`, `Get`, `List`, `Watch`, `Patch` with types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter resource plural\n167: - **GIVEN** the CodeInterpreter REST client\n168: - **WHEN** the resource path is constructed\n169: - **THEN** the plural form SHALL be `codeinterpreters`\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Expansion hooks\n172: \n173: The system SHALL provide empty expansion interfaces for custom method injection.\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeExpansion interface\n176: - **GIVEN** `generated_expansion.go`\n177: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeExpansion` is inspected\n178: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty interface `interface{}`\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterExpansion interface\n181: - **GIVEN** `generated_expansion.go`\n182: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterExpansion` is inspected\n183: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty interface `interface{}`\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## Scheme\n188: \n189: ### Requirement: Scheme registration\n190: \n191: The system SHALL register all `runtime/v1alpha1` types with a shared `Scheme`, `Codecs`, and `ParameterCodec`.\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: register.go builds Scheme\n194: - **GIVEN** `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go`\n195: - **WHEN** the package is loaded\n196: - **THEN** `Scheme`, `Codecs`, and `ParameterCodec` SHALL be initialized as package-level variables\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: AddToScheme registers v1alpha1 types\n199: - **GIVEN** `AddToScheme` is called on a `*runtime.Scheme`\n200: - **WHEN** registration completes\n201: - **THEN** all `runtime/v1alpha1` types (AgentRuntime, AgentRuntimeList, CodeInterpreter, CodeInterpreterList) SHALL be registered\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## Informer Factory\n206: \n207: ### Requirement: SharedInformerFactory interface\n208: \n209: The system SHALL provide a shared informer factory for cache-based event distribution.\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: SharedInformerFactory contract\n212: - **GIVEN** the `SharedInformerFactory` interface in `informers/externalversions/factory.go`\n213: - **WHEN** the interface is inspected\n214: - **THEN** it SHALL embed `internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory` and declare `Start`, `Shutdown`, `WaitForCacheSync`, `ForResource`, `InformerFor`, and `Runtime()` methods\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: NewSharedInformerFactory constructor\n217: - **GIVEN** a `versioned.Interface` client and `defaultResync time.Duration`\n218: - **WHEN** `NewSharedInformerFactory(client, defaultResync)` is called\n219: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `SharedInformerFactory` with the provided resync interval\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions\n222: - **GIVEN** a client, resync duration, and options (`WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`)\n223: - **WHEN** `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options...)` is called\n224: - **THEN** it SHALL return a configured `SharedInformerFactory` applying all provided options\n225: \n226: ### Requirement: Start/Shutdown/WaitForCacheSync lifecycle\n227: \n228: The system SHALL manage informer lifecycle through start, shutdown, and cache sync operations.\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Start begins informer goroutines\n231: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` with registered informers\n232: - **WHEN** `Start(stopCh)` is called\n233: - **THEN** all registered informers SHALL begin watching their resources until `stopCh` is closed\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: Shutdown stops all informers\n236: - **GIVEN** a running `SharedInformerFactory`\n237: - **WHEN** `Shutdown()` is called\n238: - **THEN** all informers SHALL be stopped and resources released\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync blocks until caches are ready\n241: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` with started informers\n242: - **WHEN** `WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)` is called\n243: - **THEN** it SHALL block until all informers have synced their caches or `stopCh` is closed, returning a `map[reflect.Type]bool`\n244: \n245: ### Requirement: Group and version accessors\n246: \n247: The system SHALL provide hierarchical accessors for group → version → informer navigation.\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: Runtime() returns group interface\n250: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`\n251: - **WHEN** `factory.Runtime()` is called\n252: - **THEN** it SHALL return `externalversionsruntime.Interface`\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: V1alpha1() returns version interface\n255: - **GIVEN** a group `Interface`\n256: - **WHEN** `group.V1alpha1()` is called\n257: - **THEN** it SHALL return `v1alpha1.Interface` with `AgentRuntimes()` and `CodeInterpreters()` accessors\n258: \n259: ### Requirement: Per-type informers\n260: \n261: The system SHALL provide informer and lister access for each resource type.\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInformer interface\n264: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeInformer` interface\n265: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n266: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer` and `Lister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister`\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: NewAgentRuntimeInformer constructor\n269: - **GIVEN** a `versioned.Interface` client and `resync time.Duration`\n270: - **WHEN** `NewAgentRuntimeInformer(client, namespace, resync, indexers)` is called\n271: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `cache.SharedIndexInformer` watching AgentRuntime resources\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer\n274: - **GIVEN** a client, namespace, resync, indexers, and `tweakListOptions`\n275: - **WHEN** `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer` is called\n276: - **THEN** it SHALL return an informer with list options modified by `tweakListOptions`\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterInformer mirrors AgentRuntimeInformer\n279: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterInformer` interface\n280: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n281: - **THEN** it SHALL declare the same methods as `AgentRuntimeInformer` but returning `CodeInterpreterLister`\n282: \n283: ### Requirement: Generic resource routing\n284: \n285: The system SHALL route GVR lookups to the correct typed informer.\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: ForResource routes agentruntimes\n288: - **GIVEN** `ForResource(v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\"))`\n289: - **WHEN** the method is called\n290: - **THEN** it SHALL return `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()` wrapped in a `GenericInformer`\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: ForResource routes codeinterpreters\n293: - **GIVEN** `ForResource(v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\"))`\n294: - **WHEN** the method is called\n295: - **THEN** it SHALL return `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()` wrapped in a `GenericInformer`\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: ForResource returns error for unknown resource\n298: - **GIVEN** `ForResource` with an unrecognized GVR\n299: - **WHEN** the method is called\n300: - **THEN** it SHALL return `(nil, error)`\n301: \n302: ### Requirement: internalinterfaces\n303: \n304: The system SHALL define base factory interfaces for informer construction.\n305: \n306: #### Scenario: NewInformerFunc signature\n307: - **GIVEN** the `internalinterfaces` package\n308: - **WHEN** `NewInformerFunc` is inspected\n309: - **THEN** it SHALL be `func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer`\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n312: - **GIVEN** the `internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory` interface\n313: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n314: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})` and `InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer`\n315: \n316: #### Scenario: TweakListOptionsFunc\n317: - **GIVEN** the `TweakListOptionsFunc` type\n318: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n319: - **THEN** it SHALL be `func(*metav1.ListOptions)`\n320: \n321: ---\n322: \n323: ## Listers\n324: \n325: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeLister\n326: \n327: The system SHALL provide a read-only caching layer for AgentRuntime objects.\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeLister interface\n330: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeLister` interface in `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n331: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n332: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)`, `AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister`, and `AgentRuntimeListerExpansion`\n333: \n334: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface\n335: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` interface\n336: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n337: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)`, `Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)`, and `AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion`\n338: \n339: #### Scenario: NewAgentRuntimeLister uses correct GroupResource\n340: - **GIVEN** `NewAgentRuntimeLister(indexer cache.Indexer)` is called\n341: - **WHEN** the lister is created\n342: - **THEN** it SHALL use `runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()` for error reporting\n343: \n344: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterLister\n345: \n346: The system SHALL provide a read-only caching layer for CodeInterpreter objects with the same pattern.\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterLister interface\n349: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterLister` interface\n350: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n351: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `List`, `CodeInterpreters(namespace) CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister`, and `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion`\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: NewCodeInterpreterLister uses correct GroupResource\n354: - **GIVEN** `NewCodeInterpreterLister(indexer)` is called\n355: - **WHEN** the lister is created\n356: - **THEN** it SHALL use `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()`\n357: \n358: ### Requirement: Lister expansion interfaces\n359: \n360: The system SHALL provide empty expansion interfaces for all lister types.\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: All four expansion interfaces are empty\n363: - **GIVEN** `expansion_generated.go`\n364: - **WHEN** the file is inspected\n365: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeListerExpansion`, `AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion`, `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion`, and `CodeInterpreterNamespaceListerExpansion` SHALL all be empty interfaces\n366: \n367: ---\n368: \n369: ## Fake Clients\n370: \n371: ### Requirement: Fake typed clients\n372: \n373: The system SHALL provide in-memory fake implementations of typed interfaces for testing.\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: Fake runtime group client\n376: - **GIVEN** `fake/fake_runtime_client.go`\n377: - **WHEN** the `FakeRuntimeV1alpha1` struct is inspected\n378: - **THEN** it SHALL implement `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` and embed `*testing.Fake`\n379: \n380: #### Scenario: Fake AgentRuntime client\n381: - **GIVEN** `fake/fake_agentruntime.go`\n382: - **WHEN** the fake AgentRuntime client is inspected\n383: - **THEN** it SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeInterface` using `*testing.Fake` actions\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: Fake CodeInterpreter client\n386: - **GIVEN** `fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go`\n387: - **WHEN** the fake CodeInterpreter client is inspected\n388: - **THEN** it SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterInterface` using `*testing.Fake` actions\n389: \n390: ### Requirement: Fake clientset\n391: \n392: The system SHALL provide a fake `Clientset` for integration testing without a real API server.\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: NewSimpleClientset creates fake clientset with objects\n395: - **GIVEN** `fake.NewSimpleClientset(objects...)` is called with initial runtime objects\n396: - **WHEN** the fake clientset is returned\n397: - **THEN** it SHALL contain the provided objects in its tracker and implement `versioned.Interface`\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: NewClientset creates fake clientset with custom reactor\n400: - **GIVEN** `fake.NewClientset(client, objects...)` is called\n401: - **WHEN** the fake clientset is returned\n402: - **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `*restclient.RESTClient` and tracker\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: Fake clientset Scheme registration\n405: - **GIVEN** `fake/register.go`\n406: - **WHEN** the package is loaded\n407: - **THEN** it SHALL wire the same scheme as the real clientset for type recognition\n408: \n409: ---\n410: \n411: ## Regeneration\n412: \n413: ### Requirement: make gen-client target\n414: \n415: The system SHALL provide a Makefile target to regenerate all client-go code.\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: make gen-client runs update-codegen.sh\n418: - **GIVEN** the Makefile defines `gen-client`\n419: - **WHEN** `make gen-client` is executed\n420: - **THEN** it SHALL invoke `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n421: \n422: #### Scenario: update-codegen.sh uses correct code-generator version\n423: - **GIVEN** `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n424: - **WHEN** the script is inspected\n425: - **THEN** it SHALL use `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1\n426: \n427: #### Scenario: code-generator flags include --with-watch\n428: - **GIVEN** the code-generator invocation in `update-codegen.sh`\n429: - **WHEN** the command is inspected\n430: - **THEN** it SHALL include `--with-watch` flag for watch support\n431: \n432: #### Scenario: output package is correct\n433: - **GIVEN** the code-generator invocation\n434: - **WHEN** the output package flag is inspected\n435: - **THEN** it SHALL be `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ## File Index\n440: \n441: ### Requirement: All generated files exist at expected paths\n442: \n443: The system SHALL produce the following file structure under `client-go/`.\n444: \n445: #### Scenario: Clientset files\n446: - **GIVEN** code generation completes\n447: - **THEN** the following files SHALL exist:\n448:   - `clientset/versioned/clientset.go`\n449:   - `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go`\n450:   - `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go`\n451:   - `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go`\n452:   - `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go`\n453:   - `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go`\n454: \n455: #### Scenario: Typed client files\n456: - **GIVEN** code generation completes\n457: - **THEN** the following files SHALL exist:\n458:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`\n459:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n460:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n461:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go`\n462:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go`\n463:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go`\n464:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go`\n465:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go`\n466:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go`\n467: \n468: #### Scenario: Informer files\n469: - **GIVEN** code generation completes\n470: - **THEN** the following files SHALL exist:\n471:   - `informers/externalversions/factory.go`\n472:   - `informers/externalversions/generic.go`\n473:   - `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`\n474:   - `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`\n475:   - `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n476:   - `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n477:   - `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`\n478: \n479: #### Scenario: Lister files\n480: - **GIVEN** code generation completes\n481: - **THEN** the following files SHALL exist:\n482:   - `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n483:   - `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n484:   - `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go`\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: ## File Changes\n489: \n490: | Action | File | Description |\n491: |--------|------|-------------|\n492: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n493: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n494: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n495: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n496: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n497: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n498: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n499: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n500: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n501: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expan